com.thedemgel.regions.api

Class RegionAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thedemgel.regions.api.RegionAPI

  • public final class RegionAPI
extends Object
    The general API to be used to access Regions from other plugins. Most functions should be available through this API, if for some reason a function is not available, please let a developer know and a solution will likely be added.

    • Method Detail

      • registerFeature

        public static void registerFeature(org.spout.api.plugin.Plugin plugin,
                   Class<? extends Feature> feature)
        Register your feature with Regions, this process will automatically register any Event listed with Spout to be fired in the WorldRegionComponent and thus be pasted to the Features attached to Regions. This method will use the Default EventParser.
        Parameters:
        plugin - Plugin that is registering the feature.
        feature - Feature being Registered

      • registerFeature

        public static void registerFeature(org.spout.api.plugin.Plugin plugin,
                   Class<? extends Feature> feature,
                   EventParser parser)
        Register your feature with Regions, this process will automatically register any Event listed with Spout to be fired in the WorldRegionComponent and thus be pasted to the Features attached to Regions. This method will use the EventParser that is pasted to it.
        Parameters:
        plugin - Plugin that is registering the feature.
        feature - Featuring being registered.
        parser - Custom EventParsering being used in registering this feature.

      • selectRegion

        public static Region selectRegion(org.spout.api.entity.Player player,
                  String regionname,
                  org.spout.api.plugin.Plugin plugin)
                           throws RegionNotFoundException,
                                  SelectionCancelledException
        Will search for and return a region by String name and place that into Players selected region slot.
        Parameters:
        player - Player selecting the region.
        regionname - The String name of the region being selected.
        plugin - Plugin attempting to allow player to select Region.
        Returns:
        Region that was selected
        Throws:
        RegionNotFoundException - Exception thrown if String region name is not found.
        SelectionCancelledException - Thrown when Event fired by select region is canceled.

      • updateRegion

        public static Region updateRegion(org.spout.api.entity.Player player)
                           throws PointsNotSetException,
                                  RegionNotFoundException
        Will attempt to update a currently loaded region, this will only work if the region was previously selected and is loaded into the players selected Region slot. Will throw RegionNotFoundException if region was not previously loaded, and will throw PointsNotSetException if all points are not correctly set.
        Parameters:
        player - The player updating their selected region.
        Returns:
        The Region Updated.
        Throws:
        PointsNotSetException - Thrown if all Points are not set.
        RegionNotFoundException - Thrown if region is a New region.

      • createRegion

        public static Region createRegion(org.spout.api.entity.Player player)
                           throws PointsNotSetException,
                                  RegionAlreadyExistsException
        This will attempt to create the region that is in the Players selected region slot. Will return with PointsNotSetException if all points of the Volume are not set correctly, and will throw RegionAlreadyExistsException if the Region had previously been created (player will need to use updateRegion instead)
        Parameters:
        player - The player attempting to create the region.
        Returns:
        The region created.
        Throws:
        PointsNotSetException - Thrown if all points are not set.
        RegionAlreadyExistsException - Region is not a new Region, update instead.

      • newRegion

        public static void newRegion(org.spout.api.entity.Player player)
        Attempt to create a new blank region. This region is not saved until createRegion is called and will not effect the world in any way until it is saved. Once saved it will immediately effect the world as it was created.
        Parameters:
        player - Player Object of player attempting to create Region.

      • setSelectedVolumeType

        public static Class<? extends Volume> setSelectedVolumeType(org.spout.api.entity.Player player,
                                            String volumeString)
                                                     throws VolumeTypeNotFoundException
        Sets the VolumeType of the Volume in the players Selected Region Slot. This will reset the bounds of the Region Volume immediately. Will return a VolumeTypeNotFoundException if the Volume type is not found in the registered Volume Types.
        Parameters:
        player - The player attempting to set VolumeType.
        volumeString - String name of the Volume being set.
        Returns:
        The Class of the Volume to be set
        Throws:
        VolumeTypeNotFoundException - Thrown when Volume type is not found.
